[{"id":"3efb9959-0143-4044-88f1-26e2528f88c6","publicName":"10-112-20-21-24-25-37-38-39-40-41-42-43-55-56-59-60-61-62-63-75-76-77-78-79-80-81-82-9-98-99","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["00F5A524-1F4A-4318-9D53-9A3F42EAAD78","0FAA4D28-2B56-40A5-A79C-E534A07D98ED","184B517E-9DEF-44B4-9EA8-E45CC96DB776","26532674-FF2E-46C9-9AB9-8F7F5EF2BE9D","2CADF229-A5B1-420C-9A58-0D72FE71FDCD","2D929612-B1FD-4AC4-BA12-494ADDCBB442","32B217C1-08DF-4196-87E6-6B0B30CD93BA","389E01FC-0600-42E2-82FF-BEF3B23C6105","3B01946F-38F5-4E26-A0C1-85C92127D906","3CB9AF64-6F72-4629-A428-E956567BE819","3F69D3A0-1915-4E8E-AB3F-8F3961B64F10","474699E9-04AC-4A57-BDE4-DFD3E1F05E62","4ADCB7E9-CFDB-462F-B6FB-E787CF1EA2C6","4DE3A677-9C07-4804-A22B-82C01AE9BB64","54577AA3-268F-4B10-8977-AB30C4206728","5BAE9C3B-51C2-4149-964B-C9C13F94E4A5","61E64E4C-03E7-433B-B273-22BF6C97E026","6BA1B136-8A8E-4987-83B3-F2DDDDB2DFB7","74C9EF65-0B33-4764-A2BF-0B2F71F0110E","83E646AA-35CC-4D48-ACD4-A9DD165D0FA0","851AFED0-5CE2-4E56-8465-F4FC73BF8FE7","8F48A7FC-A784-473E-BD34-0F789B505D14","A2D787FE-207C-489C-83F1-63715DEF6E7A","B53342B7-BE91-47AD-81A7-21E7074B3FF3","B65805C7-DE42-4F35-BDEE-14E7D6B7605A","BCFFEB80-C915-40FF-985D-5D7C7B99586A","D15B6420-1FC0-4130-9AD2-760FD3F31DCD","D47A1D59-69BD-4DEE-9E6A-FCB28AC581B1","E4DE90A5-20FE-4A8F-B297-163BA41C19C9","EEE05A8E-51CF-4AF4-9509-EC7C64D14D20","F9BD77AC-C360-47DF-8195-D16A4C65DE30"],"areaId":"a583a236cd42900e230d5b58afd0d15171e4a268b4063b3fcd7eb1f28d84157a","forecaster":"Ben Pritchett","issueDateTime":"2026-04-29T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>You might trigger a small avalanche in the storm snow on slopes steeper than about 35 degrees. Watch for cracking as a sign of unstable snow. Steer around steep features where an avalanche could sweep you off your feet and into consequential terrain below.<\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"c3a6a336-2e86-4c0a-a0cb-1f44e9166063","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777063177\/AvIDfx\/on1yipjgj0aojtzywcxp.webp","width":1194,"height":1994,"credit":"","caption":"<p>If you find stiff areas of drifted snow you could trigger a small avalanche. These avalanches could be dangerous if you get knocked off your feet and tumble down the slope, especially in consequential terrain.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A small avalanche in steep terrain.","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T20:39:41.966Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"5bb2474f-43e2-477f-bebc-5acceee9c502","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777063203\/AvIDfx\/nbrpvlgyeofdeuacdn2n.webp","width":1536,"height":2048,"credit":"","caption":"<p>A small avalanche triggered in the wrong place can quickly turn a good day into a bad one. Luckily for this rider, they avoided getting carried into the rocks. This avalanche was small, but it did manage to knock a backcountry traveler off their feet, and it was triggered in an area of firm, wind-drifted snow near the top of the slope. Assess the reactivity of these stiffened slabs by looking for cracking in drifted features. It's also a good idea to look below to assess the consequences of taking a small ride before committing to a steep slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A skier looking up at a freshly triggered avalanche in a gully. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-18T20:40:06.251Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"d0ba5296-7ff8-4892-9d83-1f60863f257d","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777063225\/AvIDfx\/gf7kmjvklwriewi7ehzr.webp","width":600,"height":600,"credit":"","caption":"<p>If riding in steeper terrain, manage your sluff so you don't get knocked down or swept into consequential terrain features. Any avalanche will likely be small, but even a small avalanche can quickly turn a good day into a bad one if triggered in extreme terrain.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small sluff in steep gully","dateTaken":"2026-04-16T20:40:34.716Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"moderate","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-01T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"moderate","tln":"moderate","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-02T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"stormSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","e_alp","ne_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"stormSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","e_alp","ne_alp","se_alp","n_tln","ne_tln","e_tln"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"2.0"}},{"type":"dryLoose","aspectElevations":["n_tln","n_alp","ne_tln","ne_alp","e_alp","e_tln","se_alp"],"likelihood":"likely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"wetLoose","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp","e_tln","ne_tln","n_tln","se_tln","s_alp","s_tln"],"likelihood":"likely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}]]}},{"id":"677a75db-815b-45e7-b325-191f3b82eb2b","publicName":"1-100-101-103-109-111-114-115-146-147-15-16-22-23-27-28-47-57-58-68-7-8","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["0BFCE84E-A2A4-4986-BF7D-84C1A0A2E467","0EF68DA6-9B2C-4366-BF30-4256AE6340BA","20D852D8-E47A-4447-ABE2-05E5F5E022D0","21F30165-D180-48B5-A36F-830F4DA1E8ED","30232C29-4A0C-4D7A-B951-EF7B873C2CBF","46C849AB-16F5-441C-9320-D501C858D14A","59C37E11-7808-47BD-9C61-8D4F6F7F2A04","72121255-B904-4013-887A-6A179A9C128B","7CC67C5D-EB4A-4F64-B82C-280ECE3C7F3C","85EBF9CD-C3F3-440B-8078-35A764C4FB9A","8DE3AC50-C0E1-417D-9F44-70F6A8F75F31","90E4159E-4E27-45EA-BA30-7A3D1894BE39","9F9C1CD8-E0D0-41B0-BD76-6BCC5DA8033E","A2D10799-F26B-475F-A19D-558A8B316594","A673FFED-CD79-4281-8CF4-AA2432ACFA2B","AC2CF19C-8218-433B-BF5A-994FCEA118FE","C37659DF-724F-4A19-B0F3-C3B490F20E56","D77686B4-1A5C-4D39-8EE8-7F8A53FCC702","DD137A25-003B-48F7-903C-0F8ECC273F8E","DE3D5E00-3003-4912-8C5C-7E6E1D752490","EE15BE29-A2EF-4CAD-A0A4-C05CC09E4549","EFE54733-51A7-48EE-B871-EE798C6197AA"],"areaId":"894e51d2c85fc4bf770c35add465d964d9545724dff415a9514abfeb6d48a670","forecaster":"Ben Pritchett","issueDateTime":"2026-04-29T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"noForecast","tln":"noForecast","btl":"noForecast","date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"noForecast","tln":"noForecast","btl":"noForecast","date":"2026-05-01T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"noForecast","tln":"noForecast","btl":"noForecast","date":"2026-05-02T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[],[],[]]}},{"id":"7b6cde09-5dc3-4289-9996-3e6fb6aa1625","publicName":"102-113-116-126-137","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["143F9D35-8EA3-49C4-812D-D87C0A6DD0F4","1D7238EB-F0EA-4A4C-A425-2F10917D7645","5E3087F6-0962-463C-B1DC-D702EC792F3B","A03BDED3-E2F8-4E90-815E-397C421D386E","A1C44D1C-F76B-4597-832C-BA12E47501AF"],"areaId":"f6b8cecb6aa6faef740ee1c8f0c41c420ef79b857a5f6cb27769814e515fb0ef","forecaster":"Chris Dickson","issueDateTime":"2026-04-29T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Most terrain in this area is safe from avalanches due to the lack of snow. But an upslope storm on Thursday could quickly change that picture and increase the avalanche danger. The hazard will rise during the day as snow accumulates, and once more than a foot of snow has fallen on slick, old-snow surfaces, it'll become possible to trigger avalanches on slopes steeper than about 35 degrees. <\/p><p>Be on the lookout for cracking in the new snow as a sign that it is becoming stiff enough to slide. Also, be aware that the new snow may conceal hazards such as rocks and stumps just below the surface. <\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"a87885c8-82b6-4ba8-8085-67002038c646","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777495253\/AvIDfx\/herumzp9sbxekdti8oce.webp","width":1002,"height":988,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Just like April, May is coming in strong with a significant winter storm. The Sangre de Cristo Range and Pikes Peak are favored to get up to 2 feet of new snow, which will drive an increase in avalanche danger. The most dangerous areas will be where you find more than a foot of new snow on slopes steeper than 35 degrees. <\/p>","tag":"snowpack","altText":"The WRF model snowfall map. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-29T19:18:01.113Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"82d17b7c-8346-41d0-a03d-57c952dafc0e","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777407132\/AvIDfx\/myy5rztwdwj6zkkkfnwf.webp","width":800,"height":600,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This picture is from April 19th, showing conditions near Blanca Peak. Most snow coverage is limited to low points in the terrain and in rocky crevices. Credit to <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"http:\/\/14ers.com\">14ers.com<\/a> user WMagnuson7. <\/p>","tag":"snowpack","altText":"Mountains with small patches of snow on them. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-19T16:49:35Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"df98cb7f-eb6a-4a12-af62-c8c5d7e811c2","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777490570\/AvIDfx\/tfi4iwstoqs6xlskqmhh.webp","width":1670,"height":1252,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Here's a shot from Glen Cove on Pikes Peak showing just how little snow there is and how patchy it is. The most dangerous areas will be where the new snow lands on old, firm snow. <\/p>","tag":"snowpack","altText":"Sparse snow cover on a mountain slope. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-28T19:24:17.216Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"considerable","tln":"moderate","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-01T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"moderate","tln":"moderate","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-02T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"stormSlab","aspectElevations":["nw_alp","e_alp","ne_alp","n_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"stormSlab","aspectElevations":["nw_alp","e_alp","ne_alp","n_alp","e_tln","ne_tln","n_tln","nw_tln"],"likelihood":"likely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"2.0"}}],[{"type":"stormSlab","aspectElevations":["nw_alp","e_alp","ne_alp","n_alp","e_tln","ne_tln","n_tln","nw_tln"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"2.0"}}]]}},{"id":"ab28897d-112a-41c2-8ab8-4beff0bb48bc","publicName":"117-118-119-120-121-122-123-124-125-127-128-129-130-131-132-133-134-135-136-138-139-140-141-142-143-144-145","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["0E5A5DFF-7518-494A-AD5E-7C20A1F98FFD","242191AB-2749-4585-A09B-C274A1C196D8","288624C3-E0C0-4816-86A1-57B068E20D5F","428340C8-91A8-480A-8FB8-322EAB7CD9EB","4765FB8A-C436-45FA-9684-6E79CF4C6ECD","568FD9F5-9079-4965-BD83-8DD1577C9141","5F219827-0BDB-4106-924F-2483CCFB5F51","674FEC54-6A25-4F1B-9201-B145C6C609E0","6952335B-D6BA-4FD0-BE76-0D1012DCF708","6BE87E45-0574-4512-907F-EC3B9EBCA365","80965A3A-9069-422B-BD91-E0EABDFD44FE","8908D9DD-0DED-4577-A8B4-6D8E48407182","93EA98DD-4165-4B8D-97F7-FE0774706466","98E60E8A-5124-454F-9660-9B879AE63B09","A3B7D9A2-121A-41EA-B824-ADCB4B1323A3","B4DBB658-8373-4DAB-8D42-7ABA0564AF9E","CB25CEAA-D3C0-416C-B11B-60B3BFF39F34","D6E3810F-1A94-4173-A5AD-147EEC39E464","D7362528-9E1C-4B04-ACEA-70E4F9BFB8B7","DBC40A27-66D6-4C9D-927E-1D5F05092F1A","E687FCD9-066C-4E47-8B6C-164C1B586A18","EC9276F5-8C4A-431C-882B-4BA90A9D8881","ECA6DAA1-1E5C-4D1F-8186-B9969A5E9EAD","EEF9E8C9-3899-4E76-8A11-C2265812FA53","F2A935D9-8E28-4421-8382-837E3E0E99B7","FCDD2204-2B10-4061-8CDF-928C5DE4C24D","FD36A9C3-DDBD-43BF-BA4B-AE2D2C8CA87F"],"areaId":"22a48c3003752289e2e99b9417ba59d61d8ec23d655fa1f7ea31cd0aa9a7c6de","forecaster":"Chris Dickson","issueDateTime":"2026-04-29T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Recent snowfall has settled out, and conditions are generally safe on most slopes. If you are pushing into extreme terrain, keep in mind that even a small slide can ruin your day if it carries you into a terrain trap, like rocks or a cliff.<\/p><p>Cooler, unsettled weather puts an end to any potential wet avalanche problems for Thursday. Another storm arrives Thursday night, but it likely won't produce enough new snow to increase the danger. <\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"04948dfd-b89d-409a-abdc-514bcf383302","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777408050\/AvIDfx\/txcfp7ynqlqzuagvidze.webp","width":950,"height":1263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>In the upper-left corner of this image, you can see our latest skier-triggered avalanche from April 27th, which flushed all the new snow down the couloir. The next day, on April 28th, many folks travelled in very similar terrain without incident. Immediately after every spring storm, you are most likely to trigger an avalanche in the new snow. But as time passes, warm temperatures and the high sun angle promote bonding and reduce the reactivity of these new snow avalanche problems. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Ski tracks in couloirs down a steep sunny mountainside. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-28T20:27:54.8Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"a963ce86-d115-48b5-b4fa-ca1d3a8fd921","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777320200\/AvIDfx\/tk1vas0w2obffqjw5qlv.webp","width":330,"height":330,"credit":"","caption":"<p>It sure is nice to see fresh snow, especially at the very end of April! The last storm dropped 6-12\" of wet heavy snow across the high country. This new snow has settled out and melted back to bare ground on many lower-elevation slopes. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A ruler measuring new snow. ","dateTaken":"2026-04-27T20:03:25.114Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"059aead1-a5dd-4a08-b3d6-f0fd3f36370e","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777060055\/AvIDfx\/rzuw7fni1jb55ixj7f9c.webp","width":1194,"height":1994,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Avalanche conditions are generally safe, but avalanches remain possible anytime there is snow on the mountains. Even a small avalanche could be dangerous if it wipes you off your feet in extreme terrain.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A snowboarder cuts across a steep slope with a fracture line of an avalanche above them. They are in the middle of a crumbling wind slab avalanche","dateTaken":"2026-04-15T19:48:00.97Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"b5f6f466-4e03-49ab-9735-1611171ca262","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777060243\/AvIDfx\/wlrzjkvxpztzssu4jbuf.webp","width":1536,"height":2048,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This avalanche was small, but it did manage to knock a backcountry traveller off their feet, and it was triggered in an area of firm, wind-drifted snow near the top of the slope. Assess the reactivity of these stiffened slabs by looking for cracking in drifted features. It's also a good idea to look below to assess the consequences of taking a small ride before committing to a steep slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A backcountry rider stands in a ravine with rocks to their left, snow to their right, and an avalanche debris pile above them.","dateTaken":"2026-04-18T19:50:49.006Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-01T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-02T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[],[],[]]}},{"id":"c45cae79-cc8a-48db-bc66-8859a07d2305","publicName":"104-105-106-107-108-11-110-12-13-14-17-18-19-2-26-29-3-30-31-32-33-34-35-36-4-44-45-46-48-49-5-50-51-52-53-54-6-64-65-66-67-69-70-71-72-73-74-83-84-85-86-87-88-89-90-91-92-93-94-95-96-97","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["002F1CBA-C06D-4135-A893-FC464013B62B","028E2912-5D1A-4EC6-A22D-2180A797ECDD","031F974D-8D27-40AF-9646-0D96A728826F","071639C0-9D38-49C1-8AF3-F227A80F447D","07217D33-65CD-450C-870A-EC2693445190","14EEEAD3-1AC2-4C19-A8F7-36AD6060F101","1660315E-6000-4E83-BF42-36B71129C6B1","1EAF86F5-A2D8-44B7-A485-CF625FC37C72","24890DB8-FD42-4988-80B7-82367FD5E8F1","30C5E3BC-D260-4F9E-B46D-717CCBA6C77E","3194EF47-46C9-4132-83C1-D156F9B94123","3302D495-0B02-4C2B-B7E2-04A5BC6B732E","34FE3430-9CD0-4470-891D-E54D8C2A4E29","35FB8EF6-E22C-48A4-89FA-6FCD49920345","383548A5-2C8E-4CC6-985E-83F7AE17EAB6","3C27CD1A-FD13-48B3-B0FF-A5947832FBEB","40CAA2D1-6467-40BA-A652-5E1EBE1AABBB","4481315B-A3B2-430F-AD25-51F077D30A1A","464239AD-281A-4E5E-825C-AA4A668FBBCC","468B78D0-198E-4FA4-A2CD-09F436CBA5EE","4696EB06-4EE3-42DD-B53A-29C3735AD595","49B9973C-4E52-4B70-A4A9-4718AFB95868","4FB2A5B0-EE82-4734-86BD-AECECDA73A07","53EAF595-DF1F-461E-974A-046F08ABC33D","59DA954B-77EC-49A4-B270-169CACB0E2EE","5AD4C8BF-731F-4B70-8A78-C3D3151A85DD","6AFB830C-8B2B-4293-AA7A-C872944C2263","6C566741-E85D-427F-8D65-9DC8B58DBCE5","71056143-E59C-42C0-8E82-43F29CC720C4","7183F4E9-26AF-4D12-9B99-A4B42A3D01A3","72283DBC-55B0-4638-A44E-7420893000C5","7696EB7F-C450-4967-B4BF-C4928C6F82D0","7BA4F5A7-6E11-4A81-88FC-0A72429699A0","7E3F4D07-B8FB-49CB-8B24-F67304294AEA","8385ACB2-7117-4757-AB18-37F26935DF3E","865AEF1B-7C59-4771-9A78-62BD6718404A","947E5EB1-C540-4654-B72B-E92FACD4DA89","97694259-0F92-4CE6-A4C9-3A69D2C33F35","977E9661-AE8E-45A5-9882-EC28C4B149AE","98171DBD-49BD-41E6-89AD-222BC932C5CD","9AB77E3D-5C1C-4DAF-B0C5-81B066FB46AE","9D94D73F-C7DC-4C33-AF8A-1EC8A490D5A9","9DFB3103-D688-4AB3-B16D-EE6A20EA25A7","9F0C6D78-4C62-4DDA-8850-5AE4C83E2FF1","A184002D-BBFC-45DA-A94B-B64AC1B5D0E7","A50331E1-4A1D-4120-8D49-BDBD4BF7914C","AB799973-D423-4150-9486-EC2BCF7ED731","AD6B1059-5E99-43DC-B921-1DA648F30368","B6E88FB0-589D-4F0A-966F-DFF05CE159DC","B868BD7F-CC6D-418F-95EA-BD8B43354FA3","C5F1EC58-8972-45C2-9F1F-D5835EF0652C","C6D989AD-82E5-4DB9-96A4-15F364D6F09B","C835BE8E-EC55-4C2B-8B52-815C66D0209C","D5746397-17D6-4EE2-837F-6DA0AC4CD2D6","D71F4D50-11F3-4B8E-A961-6704FD21D51B","D892417F-5570-4940-A311-AA918B8A2AF7","DAFC9825-B67E-4FF5-8E6C-4D05CC20E554","E431262C-0AE0-4E4B-9DA4-A2E35B49E671","E72F7052-876D-476F-89A0-9AEE369F0317","ED5C21DE-D335-4D82-85CF-485CD449C602","FCEB8EE2-B8A0-44E8-ABD9-EEED4EDDDAA7","FE996429-CEFA-41FC-8228-3E4661406DDF"],"areaId":"6ade76a5decc12b1290d9df77d48ebcbaec98677ae333ce41d77181198fc9839","forecaster":"Kreston Rohrig","issueDateTime":"2026-04-29T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Recent avalanche problems have quickly healed, and most slopes are safe to travel on. In areas that received more snowfall from recent storms, look out for small pockets of lingering wind-drifted snow. Consider the consequences of being caught in a small avalanche before you travel on slopes steeper than around 40 degrees.<\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"b7be55af-5972-46f5-a60f-3e353211b962","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777491723\/AvIDfx\/tsycftswkje8ocapo16x.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Look for small pockets of wind-drifted snow as the ongoing hazard you need to manage if riding in very steep terrain where even a small avalanche could carry you down through trees or rocks.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small avalanches near ski tracks","dateTaken":"2026-04-27T19:43:39.519Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"007f83ca-d0de-4d25-a4c0-2492a1bdd533","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777491830\/AvIDfx\/tp4rkbvntxxeimxlwl7f.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Be heads-up for small pockets of stiffer wind-drifted snow if riding in extreme or consequential terrain, where taking a small ride could be dangerous.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"The crown of a small avalanche","dateTaken":"2026-04-28T19:44:08.635Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"b135bedc-f651-4705-97e5-258ae3e474a5","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777491954\/AvIDfx\/zht9gyfkgfdpqwnnursz.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Check slopes thoroughly before committing if you plan to ride in steeper terrain. Lingering pockets of snow could catch you by surprise and trip you up if you aren't careful.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Debris from a small avalanche","dateTaken":"2026-04-28T19:46:10.237Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-30T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-01T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-02T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["ne_alp","e_alp","n_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[],[]]}}]